6:
Phew... That should be the last of it
for today!
10:
Looks like someone's in a good
mood! Did you have fun too?
14:
N-no way! It was nothing... really! I'm
just looking forward to today's
meetup with my fellow writers...
18:
It's a show and tell of our finds from
the last expo... Hehe.
30:
I-it's... ummm. How should I put it? A
gathering? A gathering for... books... I
mean for authors! Up-and-coming
ones, mainly.
34:
I would like to read some of these
books.
42:
Hehe, of course you can join!
Everyone is welcome here—the
more, the merrier!
49:
By the way, Meryll! Is this the outfit I
keep hearing about around town? It
really does look cute on you!
51:
Rumor has it Meryll decided to give
up penning romance novels and is
hoping to star in one instead! She's
certainly turning more heads than
ever before, hehe.
55:
E-excuse me! I'm doing nothing of
the sort. I'm only wearing this outfit
for a job, I'll have you know!
59:
M-moving on! Let's get talking about
those finds!
62:
Hehehe... As you wish. Take a look at
this beauty!
65:
Ooh, this one is mostly illustrations,
huh? Hmm, I've never seen this
character before... Is she an
adventurer?
69:
Wow, she's so cute... but with a
pushy, flirty aura! This is some
seriously good stuff—
74: Wait a second... IS THAT ME?!
78:
What is the meaning of this?! Is this
character based on me?!
86:
It is, isn't it?! What the heck is this?!
A-are they making fun of me?!
89:
Well, you and that outfit have been
the talk of the town, so a bit of
real-world inspiration may have
seeped through...
92:
I haven't been wearing this for THAT
long! How did they draw all this so
fast?!
95:
Hmmm, now that I'm looking at it
closer, I do see the resemblance.
100: It's cute. Do you have any others?
111:
Why is Meryll wearing less clothing
in this one?
117:
BWAAAH?! I-I would never wear such
a thing! And what's with that
dialogue?! It's so VULGAR!
126:
No, no, no! Th-there's no way I'm
THIS cute! That doesn't even look like
anything I would wear!
131:
Haha. I have a good idea how you
must be feeling right now, Meryll.
133:
Long ago, my adventures also
became the subject of songs and
art. Fame is not an easy thing to
navigate.
138:
Being sung about and having
compromising pictures drawn of
you aren't even remotely the same
thing!
141:
And I can't believe that this person
didn't even consult with me about
this! The nerve!
145:
They clearly don't understand
industry etiquette! How amateurish...
148:
But then again... I do like this design
here...
152:
I suppose I have to give them
credit... the book is superb!
154:
Even though its depiction of me is...
less than accurate.
158:
This picture shows you writing
stories for children! "Fanfic pusher
Meryll corrupting the youth." Huh.
Not sure what that means, exactly...
163: P-put that down that right now!
167:
So which is it? If it's really bothering
you, we could always throw in a
complaint.
170: ...No. We don't have to go that far.
179:
I'm not the sort of person to talk ill of
another's work...
182:
I don't know what other people
would do... but I think I'll let this one
slide...
185:
In the end, it's all about fun, isn't it? I
can understand where they're
coming from.
193: ...Wait, no, not that one! Th-this is...
196:
S-Stella! Let's try reading this book
instead!
203:
Th-that's right! Don't bother with
boring stuff like that! This entry in
the "Wandering Knight" series is WAY
more interesting!
206: ...What's the genre of that other one?
209:
Uh... perhaps some things are best
left unsaid...
213:
I want to know... but I also don't.
...Or maybe I do?
